Test Cases
To ensure the correctness of the OldPhonePad method, we can create test cases that cover different scenarios and expected outputs. Here are a few examples:

Test Case 1: Basic Input
csharp
Copy code
string input = "33#";
string expectedOutput = "E";
string output = Phone.OldPhonePad(input);

// Assert
Assert.AreEqual(expectedOutput, output);
Test Case 2: Backspace
csharp
Copy code
string input = "227*#";
string expectedOutput = "B";
string output = Phone.OldPhonePad(input);

// Assert
Assert.AreEqual(expectedOutput, output);
Test Case 3: Multiple Keypad Presses
csharp
Copy code
string input = "4433555 555666#";
string expectedOutput = "HELLO";
string output = Phone.OldPhonePad(input);

// Assert
Assert.AreEqual(expectedOutput, output);
Test Case 4: Invalid Characters
csharp
Copy code
string input = "8 88777444666*664#";
string expectedOutput = "?????";
string output = Phone.OldPhonePad(input);

// Assert
Assert.AreEqual(expectedOutput, output);
